Magallanodon is a genus of mammals from the extinct group Gondwanatheria. It contains a single species, Magallanodon baikashkenke. The species is the first Mesozoic mammal known from Chile, and is Late Cretaceous in age. It is known from individual teeth found in a quarry in the RÃ­o de Las Chinas Valley located in the Magallanes Basin in Chilean Patagonia. The fossils come from the Dorotea Formation, which is Late Campanian to Early Maastrichtian in age.